        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('DHCP - Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol'); ?>
        <p>The <strong>Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol</strong> (<strong>DHCP</strong>) is a standardized networking protocol used on Internet Protocol (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('IP', '/it/networks/internet-protocol-suite/internet'); ?>) networks for dynamically distributing network configuration parameters, such as <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('IP addresses', 'it//networks/internet-protocol-suite'); ?>) for interfaces and services.</p>
        <p>With DHCP, computers request IP addresses and networking parameters automatically from a DHCP server, reducing the need for a network administrator or a user to configure these settings manually.</p>
